data.value: THE SEMESTER THAT WAS... The Peer Facilitators Association, an organization under the supervision of the Center for Guidance Services, had its team building activity last September 12, 2018. The theme was “Strengthening Peer Connection towards Empowered Leadership and Service”. The primary objective was to create a stronger bond and camaraderie among peer facilitators necessary to develop and promote helping skills and leadership.

data.name: Label9.Text
data.value: THE SEMESTER THAT WAS... The Center for Guidance Services conducted an informative and preventive seminar to promote awareness and address the use and abuse of drugs, alcohol, and tobacco among high school and college students. There were two sessions conducted last July 19, 2018, a morning and an afternoon session. However, due to inclement weather, afternoon classes were suspended on the second day, July 20, 2018. Hence, there was only a morning session.

data.name: Label8.Text
data.value: THE SEMESTER THAT WAS... The Center for Guidance Services conducted its annual training activity for students also known as Peer Mentoring Program last October 3, 2018 for HSU and October 4, 2018 for college at the Multimedia Room 507, Administration Building Health and Physical Science Building. The primary objective of the program was to equip selected students with skills in helping, communicating, problem solving, and decision making necessary to help fellow students. Through relevant talk and workshop activities, students were empowered to act as helpers and active listeners to their fellow students as they assist, process, and coordinate to the guidance counselors.

data.name: Label3.Text
data.value: Peer Facilitators Association (PFA) had its thanksgiving session and capability building activity last December 18, 2018. Joined by the officers and advisers, everyone from the organization took time to listen to the presentations based on the previous mental health seminars attended by the presenters. Fun but meaningful icebreaker activities were done in between. This event served as the organization's year-ender to cap off the year with gratitude and hope.

data.name: Label2.Text
data.value:
UMak PFA attended an informative seminar last January 31, 2019 entitled Eyes Wide Open: Exploring the Implications of Social Media Use on Mental Health Today at PUP Sta. Mesa. The event successfully raised awareness and understanding on the different issues related to the use of social media and various strategies to address it. UMak student participants actively engaged with the discussions facilitated by the knowledgeable speakers.
Bonus: Our very own Peer Facilitator, Karl from College of Education, won during the Trivia Challenge of the event organizers.
